<br>
First, you decide not to fully buff my pet (yes I have both 61 and 62 pets) that's 1500 hp and the commensurate AC it doesn't have (btw this happened in PoV to me yesterday).  Puller comes back with 2 mobs.  Enchanter attempts to mez one and unfortunately gets a resist and starts getting pummeled.  I back off pet immediately and send my trusty air pet on the golem.  Pet starts off with a stun and gives the enchanter a chance to back up and regroup and catch a heal.  Pet has aggro now.  I cast mala to help the chanter so he doesn't have to gain more aggro with tash.  Mob gets off a bunch of attacks on pet while he decides to re-mez and takes it right past enrage and it dies while he is recasting mez.  He is then attacked again and summarily eaten.  Guess who is next.  During this time I'm telling the cleric to toss the pet a quick heal but no heal came.<br>
<br>
Now if pet got Virtue it would have mitigated some of that damage due to increased AC.  It would have enraged (due to more hps) giving the cleric or me more time to heal.  But no my pet was expendable.<br>
<br>
Guess what, 2 people died because pet wasn't buffed and healed.  I asked for virtue for the pet and offered a dot but wasn't listened to--probably thought it wasn't worth the mana and time.<br>
<br>
Long story short is that people are more important than pet but the player base in general has been slow to understand the true power of our pets once fully buffed.  Air pet with virtue, SoV, BO5, weapons, and armor is one mean mother.  It can tank slowed mobs just as well a level 60 warrior without defensive maybe better with the stun component mitigating damage.  What you want to be prepared for is for the pet to off tank mobs and not a second group member like a monk so the maximum amount of damage can be focused on the main mob and you can heal the secondary tank (i.e. the pet) with out getting healing aggro.<br>
<br>
Learn that last paragraph and live it and you will REALLY love mages. <p>Master Sarridon Soulcraver<br>
